.TH GIT-REMOTE-DOKUWIKI 1 "December 2025" "git-remote-dokuwiki 0.4.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-remote-dokuwiki \- git remote helper for DokuWiki
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git clone
dokuwiki::\fIuser\fR@\fIwiki.example.com\fR[\fI/namespace\fR]
.br
.B git push
.br
.B git pull
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-remote-dokuwiki
is a git remote helper that allows you to use git to interact with a DokuWiki.
You can clone, fetch, edit, and push wiki pages just like a regular git repository.
.PP
Pages are stored as
.B .md
files with directory structure matching DokuWiki namespaces.
Media files are stored alongside pages.
Each wiki revision becomes a git commit with the original timestamp and author.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Clone an entire wiki:
.B git clone dokuwiki::user@wiki.example.com
.TP
Clone a specific namespace:
.B git clone dokuwiki::user@wiki.example.com/namespace
.TP
Shallow clone (latest revision only):
.B git clone --depth 1 dokuwiki::user@wiki.example.com
.TP
Push changes:
.nf
git add page.md
git commit -m "Update page"
git push
.fi
.TP
Dry-run push (see what would be pushed without pushing):
.B git push --dry-run
.TP
Use a different file extension:
.B git clone "dokuwiki::user@wiki.example.com?ext=txt"
.SH AUTHENTICATION
The tool uses git's credential helper system.
On first use, it will prompt for your password and store the session cookie in
.IR .git/dokuwiki-cookies.txt .
.PP
Alternatively, set the
.B DOKUWIKI_PASSWORD
environment variable.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DOKUWIKI_PASSWORD
Password for authentication. If set, skips the credential helper.
.TP
.B DOKUWIKI_COOKIE_FILE
Path to cookie file. Defaults to
.IR .git/dokuwiki-cookies.txt .
.TP
.B DOKUWIKI_VERBOSE
Set to 1 for info output, 2 for debug output.
.SH VERBOSE OUTPUT
Use git's
.B \-v
flag for progress info, or
.B \-vv
for debug output:
.PP
.nf
git fetch -v
git push -vv
.fi
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.IP \(bu 2
DokuWiki with JSON-RPC API enabled (API version 14+)
.IP \(bu 2
A user account with remote API access
.PP
To enable the remote API, add to
.IR conf/local.php :
.PP
.nf
$conf['remote'] = 1;
$conf['remoteuser'] = '@user';
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .git/dokuwiki-cookies.txt
Session cookies for authentication (Netscape format).
